-- GMR Infrastructure, Hindustan Copper, Zenith Birla: India Equity Preview
-- Vipin V. Nair
-- 2010-06-25T02:32:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-25/gmr-infrastructure-hindustan-copper-zenith-birla-india-equity-preview.html

          
          
             The following companies may have
 unusual  price changes in India  trading . Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of the  last close .  
 The Bombay Stock Exchange’s Sensitive Index, or  Sensex ,
declined 25.70, or 0.1 percent, to 17,730.24. The S&P CNX  Nifty 
Index on the National Stock Exchange fell 0.05 percent to
5,320.60. The BSE 200 Index dropped 0.1 percent to 2,243.60.  SGX
S&P CNX Nifty Index  futures for July delivery fell 0.3 percent
to 5,299 at 9:10 a.m. in Singapore today.  
 Bharat Heavy Electricals Ltd.  (BHEL IN): Alstom SA is close
to finalizing talks for a tripartite venture with state-owned
Nuclear Power Corp of India Ltd. and Bharat Heavy, the Hindu
Business Line newspaper reported, citing Alstom Power Senior
Vice-President for Thermal Products  Guy Chardon .  
 The stock’s rating was also raised to “buy” from “hold”
by Citigroup Inc. analysts led by  Venkatesh Balasubramaniam , who
said investors should switch to the company from Larsen & Toubro
Ltd. in the near term given the difference in valuations and the
relative stock performance.  Bharat Heavy , the nation’s biggest
power-equipment maker, gained 0.8 percent to 2,454.5 rupees.  
 Essar Oil Ltd.  (ESOIL IN): The company has been awarded
four coal-bed methane blocks, India’s Home Minister  Palaniappan Chidambaram  said. Essar Oil fell 1.9 percent to 129.35 rupees.  
 GMR Infrastructure Ltd.  (GMRI IN): The builder of airports
and roads said it won the bid to expand and operate the Male
International Airport in the Maldives. The mandate is for 25
years. The shares rose 0.4 percent to 56.85 rupees.  
 Hindustan Copper Ltd.  (HCP IN): India’s monopoly producer
of the metal ore will invest 45.8 billion rupees ($985 million)
in the next five to six years to expand, Chairman Shakeel Ahmed
said. Production is expected to increase to 12 million metric
tons in the period from 3.6 million tons this financial year
started in April. The company is seeking 10 new mining licenses
in India and looking to acquire reserves in Chile and Namibia,
he said. The shares rose 0.2 percent to 493.95 rupees.  
 Zenith Birla (India) Ltd.  (ZB IN): The steel pipe
manufacturer’s board approved giving one free share for every
five held, it said in a statement to the Bombay Stock Exchange.
Zenith gained 7.6 percent to 24.15 rupees.  
